    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1409"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/289.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Willard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On several occasions recently the King has pointedly questioned me regarding
                    Mexico and the suffering there of Spaniards and their <pb facs="0932" n="816"
                        xml:id="pg_816"/> interests. He has just inquired regarding the Spanish Vice
                    Consul at Tampico whom the press reports held for ransom by Constitutionalists
                    and regarding press reports that Villa has again declared he would kill all
                    Spaniards. I am to see the King Monday night and if I could reenforce the
                    reassurances (based on belated press reports and such news as I can obtain
                    otherwise) I am constantly making on appropriate occasions on my own account
                    with some pertinent message or up to date news from the Department from time to
                    time I could be more instrumental counteracting the somewhat unsympathetic and
                    aggrieved attitude of this Government. I would especially appreciate a message
                    that I could use Monday night.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
